On to finishing Lucille number two (a commission) in White Oak, my least favorite wood to work.
Everything nice about Walnut is awful with White Oak.  Not easily shaped with a rasp and scraper due to the differentiation in hardness in early wood and late wood which means I need to whip out all of the slicing tools I have.
This crazy old Millers Falls spokeshave, given to me by @joshvillegas94 when he decided to go full kanna, is the perfect tool for these inside curves. 
Nicely honed and with a steady hand, I should be finishing this one in a day or two.
